### 7. Scale & Metrics (for realistic benchmarking)

- [ ] **Total QM count** across the enterprise
- [ ] **Total channel count** (sender + receiver pairs)
- [ ] **Total queue count** by type
- [ ] **Total application count** connected to MQ
- [ ] **Message volumes** — daily/hourly throughput numbers if available
- [ ] **Average and max routing hops** for messages today
- [ ] **Any existing complexity metrics** — if the enterprise already measures MQ complexity somehow

---

### 8. Where to Look (Don't Miss These)

- **Sub-pages/child pages** under the main MQ Confluence space
- **Attached files** — Excel sheets, Visio diagrams, PDFs, MQSC scripts
- **Labels/tags** — search for tags like `mq`, `messaging`, `integration`, `middleware`
- **Comments section** — often contains real pain-point discussions from engineers
- **"Related pages" links** — Confluence often links to architecture review boards, incident reports
- **Table of contents macro** — expand every section, some may be collapsed by default
- **Embedded Jira tickets** — often linked to change requests or incidents
- **Version history** — older versions may show how the topology has evolved (useful for "organic growth" narrative)

